---
layout: post
title: Foundations — screw piles vs pads
date: 2025-09-23
tags: [shelter, foundation]
---

Context: seasonal flooding, frost ~1.5 m.

Options
- Screw piles: fast install, minimal concrete, removable.
- Concrete pads: cheap, heavy, needs sonotubes below frost.

Notes
- Elevate floor ≥60 cm above peak flood.
- Ventilated crawlspace to dry after spring.

Next steps
- Price 8–10 piles.
- Check torque spec and load.
- Confirm local permit requirements.
